<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}-{8}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.1</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}-{8}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{-{3}{x}}}\right)}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{-{3}{x}}}=-\frac{{8}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{8}}{{4}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{8}}{{4}}\right)}}}}{{-{{3}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx-{0.1}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

